Reporting the progress of personal research and solving problems appearing in the process; discussions on most important and actual topics in theoretical and practical fields of semiotics. Planning research work.  Reading and analytical presentation of classical texts in semiotics and culture theory.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Develop abilities for academic discussions, writing and research, work on practical problems in students'  research. Students introduce their PhD theses and get the relevant feedback. Every semester classical works in semiotics and cultural theory are read and reviewed by the participants. Supervisors of PhD theses participate in the seminar as well, widening options for feedback and introducing their supervisory practice to ohter students.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students:
- acquires a basic ability for self-assessment and problem solving during one's research activity;
- can make an academic presentation;
- is able to transfer one's own knowledge and research;
- obtains knowledge of classical texts and treatments in semiotics and culture theory;
- obtains abilities to carry out academic research;
- is able to present results of one's research field in oral and written form;
- is able to identify and solve occurring problems and topics in one's own research and help colleagues in these activities;
- is able to initiate and take part in academic discussions in one's field of studies, debate and defend  one's statements.
